│ patch_description        │ The current program has 18 parameters and achieves a combined score of 0.50 with test     │
│                          │ accuracy of 0.43. Analysis of the performance metrics shows:                              │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ 1. **Current strengths**: The simplified ansatz (removing the CRX gates from the prior    │
│                          │ version) improved parameter efficiency and reduced gate count, leading to better test     │
│                          │ accuracy (0.43 vs 0.35).                                                                  │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ 2. **Identified limitations**:                                                            │
│                          │    - Test accuracy is still modest at 0.43, suggesting the ansatz lacks sufficient        │
│                          │ expressivity                                                                              │
│                          │    - The current design uses only RY rotations and CZ entanglers, which is relatively     │
│                          │ restrictive                                                                               │
│                          │    - No parametrized two-qubit gates are present, limiting the circuit's ability to learn │
│                          │ complex correlations                                                                      │
│                          │    - The feature map uses only RX, and the ansatz uses only RY—adding RZ rotations can    │
│                          │ provide additional degrees of freedom                                                     │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ 3. **Proposed improvements**:                                                             │
│                          │    - **Add RZ rotations** on select qubits (corners and edges) to increase expressivity   │
│                          │ without excessive parameter growth                                                        │
│                          │    - **Reintroduce parametrized controlled rotations** but use CRZ (instead of CRX) on    │
│                          │ center-connected edges, as CRZ provides better phase-space coverage for tic-tac-toe       │
│                          │ classification                                                                            │
│                          │    - **Maintain parameter efficiency** by using selective parameter sharing: corners      │
│                          │ share one RZ parameter, edges share another                                               │
│                          │    - This adds ~6-8 new parameters while maintaining circuit depth efficiency             │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ 4. **Rationale**:                                                                         │
│                          │    - RZ gates complement RY gates and the RX feature map, providing full SU(2) coverage   │
│                          │ per qubit                                                                                 │
│                          │    - CRZ entanglers on center connections (1-8, 3-8, 5-8, 7-8) are geometrically          │
│                          │ meaningful for tic-tac-toe structure                                                      │
│                          │    - Selective sharing keeps parameter count low while allowing the circuit to learn      │
│                          │ class-specific rotations                                                                  │
│                          │    - This design balances expressivity (to improve accuracy) with parameter efficiency    │
│                          │ (to maintain generalization)                                                              │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ Expected outcome: Test accuracy should improve toward 0.50+, with combined score          │
│                          │ potentially reaching 0.55+.                                                               │
