│ patch_description        │ Propose parameter sharing for the center-edge CRX entangling gates to reduce the          │
│                          │ per-block parameter count and enforce symmetry. By reusing a single parameter across all  │
│                          │ four CRX gates that connect the center qubit (8) to the edge qubits (1,3,5,7), we         │
│                          │ decrease N_PARAMS_PER_BLOCK from 7 to 4 (3 RY params + 1 shared CRX param). This should   │
│                          │ improve generalization and training efficiency (fewer trainable parameters) while         │
│                          │ retaining the data-reuploading structure and adjacency constraints. The block remains     │
│                          │ expressive due to multiple center-edge entanglers using the same tunable strength, and    │
│                          │ symmetry is encouraged across the four connections.                                       │
