│ patch_name               │ augment_crx_split_and_duplicate_cz                                                        │
│ patch_description        │ Propose two targeted enhancements to the ANSATZ_SPEC to improve expressivity and training │
│                          │ efficiency without changing the training loop or data/feature map:                        │
│                          │ 1) Duplicate the fixed CZ entangling layer within each ansatz block to increase circuit   │
│                          │ depth and expressivity, allowing the model to capture more complex correlations in        │
│                          │ tic-tac-toe boards.                                                                       │
│                          │ 2) Split the four CRX gates that connect to the center qubit into two parameter groups    │
│                          │ (crx_left and crx_right) by sharing parameters across symmetric pairs. This increases     │
│                          │ parameter efficiency while enabling richer, symmetry-informed entanglement patterns       │
│                          │ around the center.                                                                        │
│                          │ These changes are confined to the ANSATZ_SPEC and keep adjacency constraints satisfied.   │
│                          │ They should modestly increase depth and parameter count in a controlled way, with the     │
│                          │ potential to improve validation/test performance and reduce generalization gap.           │
